# BigBit bridge allow-list (KEEP-SYNC). One line per table:
#   AccessTable | pg_target | sql_file (in sql/)
# The deny-list (EXCLUDE-TVRDO in F3) is enforced by simply NOT listing tables
# here - the script never mdb-export-s anything outside this manifest.
#
# Column order in each sql/*.sql staging table MUST match the Access table's
# storage order (mdb-export emits all columns in that order; \copy loads
# positionally after skipping the header).
#
# --- v0 pilot: 3 item classifier tables (models existed in 2.0 but were never
#     synced - items had group/subgroup/origin CODES without NAMES, F1 gap) ---
R_Grupa    | item_groups    | item_groups.sql
R_Podgrupa | item_subgroups | item_subgroups.sql
R_Poreklo  | item_origins   | item_origins.sql
#
# --- phase 2 (ID-space RESOLVED, plan 7.6 = option A). Order matters: masters
#     before Cenovnik (Cenovnik remaps item via items.external_item_id).
#
# Magacini fills warehouses (empty, NOT owned by the live MSSQL sync) -> ACTIVE.
Magacini   | warehouses     | warehouses.sql
#
# !! DEACTIVATED UNTIL CUTOVER (Nenad 2026-07-12): the 4 tables below are OWNED
#    by the live MSSQL (QBigTehn) sync. Do NOT overwrite them from BigBit while
#    that sync runs. sql/ files are authored + dry-run-clean; uncomment ONLY at
#    cutover, after the MSSQL sync is switched off (plan 7.6 "jedan pisac").
#    NOTE: dry-run shows ~all rows would "update" because BigBit carries fields
#    the MSSQL sync leaves empty (code_type_code, salesperson_id...) -> before
#    cutover activation, do a field-level diff so the guard flags only real diffs
#    (esp. items: 90984 would-update with no FK reason -> representation check).
# Komitenti  | customers          | customers.sql          (dry-run: read=6669 ins=5 upd=6230 miss=14)
# Predmeti   | projects           | projects.sql           (dry-run: read=7736 ins=6 upd=7600 miss=2)
# R_Artikli  | items              | items.sql              (UPDATE-only via external_item_id; dry-run upd=90984)
# Cenovnik   | price_list_entries | price_list_entries.sql (TODO: author; needs ple business-key unique + item remap)
#     (Prodavci: NEVER expose [Password] - plain-text; needs a projection since
#      mdb-export dumps the whole table).
